Pavoclinus pavo, the Peacock klipfish, is a species of clinid found from LÃ¼deritzbucht, Namibia to the Kei River, South Africa where it can be found in weedy areas at the low tide line.  It can reach a maximum length of 15 centimetres (5.9 in) TL.  This species feeds primarily on amphipods, isopods, gastropods and polychaete worms.